@node "Overview" "Overview of PowerView"
@next "Installation"
@prev "Main"
@{b}PowerView@{ub} is a JPEG-picture viewer for the Amigacomputer for those
of you who owns a PPC-accelerator (and is using the ppc.library from Phase5).
The JPEG conversion is based upon libjpeg V6b from the Independent JPEG Group.

I guess that's all, now enjoy!
@endnode

@node "Installation" "Installing PowerView"
@next "Requirements"
@prev "Overview"
Not much to say here really.

· Copy the executable to wherever you want it!

@endnode

@node "Requirements" "Requirements of PowerView"
@next "Usage"
@prev "Installation"
PowerView requires:
 · Workbench and Kickstart @{b}39+@{ub}
 · ppc.library @{b}46.19+@{ub}
 · PPC-accelerator

@{i}PowerView has been tested on the following setup:
 · A1200T/040@25MHz+603@240MHz/BVision/64Mb Fast
 · A1200/EC040@25MHz+603@160MHz/16 Mb Fast
@{ui}
@endnode

@node "Usage" "Using PowerView"
@next "License"
@prev "Requirements"
CLI Usage:
  @{b}PowerView FILENAME DEPTH/N SCREENMODE/S CENTER/S BESTMODE/S@{ub}

  @{b}FILENAME@{ub}     The name of the jpegfile to view
  @{b}DEPTH@{ub}        Nr of bitplanes to use (3 - 8)
  @{b}SCREENMODE@{ub}   Forces the screenmoderequester
  @{b}CENTER@{ub}       Center the image
  @{b}BESTMODE@{ub}     Let the OS choose the best screenmode

  If the program is started from CLI and not all required variables
  is given the program will read the tooltypes anyway and try to use
  the values used. If the DEPTH, MODEID, WIDTH and HEIGHT tooltypes
  are not specified an ASL requester will appear.

  The FILENAME can also be left blank when run from CLI and a ASL
  filerequester will ask for you're desired file.

ToolTypes:
  @{b}WIDTH@{ub}        The screen width
  @{b}HEIGHT@{ub}       The screen height
  @{b}DEPTH@{ub}        Nr of bitplanes (3-8)
  @{b}MODEID@{ub}       Preferred modeid
  @{b}SCREENMODE@{ub}   Force the screenmoderequester to be displayed
  @{b}CENTER@{ub}       Center the image
  @{b}BESTMODE@{ub}     Let the OS choose the best screenmode

  If the WIDTH, HEIGHT, DEPTH and MODEID tooltypes are not set a ASL
  moderequester will appear, unless the BESTMODE option is specified.
  When run and the program is started from WB a filerequester will
  always be used to specify the JPEG to view.

  Quit the program by either pressing one of the mousebuttons or by
  pressing any of the q or escape keys.

@endnode

